<meta name="dc.description" property="og:description" content="Ozone in the stratosphere is vitally important to life because it absorbs biologically harmful ultraviolet (UV) radiation coming from the sun. The principal aim of the Montreal Protocol is to protect the ozone layer by taking measures to control total global production and consumption of substances that deplete it, with the ultimate objective of their elimination on the basis of developments in scientific knowledge and technological information." />
